    "narrative": "For today\u2019s slate, our lineup leans heavily into aggressive matchups against favorable pitching, led by our standout play, **Jazz Chisholm Jr.** (77.47). Facing Severino, **Jazz Chisholm Jr.** profiles as our must-start anchor, leveraging a high-ceiling platoon advantage. Similarly, **Mickey Moniak** (75.97) and **James Wood** (73.87) are positioned for elite days; **Mickey Moniak** is effectively weaponized by an 18% park-and-platoon boost in a soft matchup against Javier, while **James Wood** thrives at the top of the order with a 10% efficiency lift. We are also capitalizing on **Trevor Story** (69.55), who benefits from a massive 19% SP skill cushion against Drohan, easily offsetting the minor 5% drag from the wind.\n\nOur most difficult bench decision involved **Austin Riley**, whose 44.09 score fell just short of the cut. While **Austin Riley** carries a strong base projection, the 19% downgrade against Detmers\u2019s xERA ultimately forced him to the bench in favor of more efficient platoon-advantaged bats like **Tyler Soderstrom**, who is soaking up a 6% platoon bonus today. We are tracking a few risks: **Zach McKinstry** (50.50) is starting despite a stiff 6% penalty for hitting in the #8 hole, though the wind blowing out at his venue provides a necessary hedge. Meanwhile, **Vinnie Pasquantino** (46.57) remains in the lineup despite a heavy 15% platoon tax against the southpaw, as his high base projection keeps him ahead of our remaining bench depth. Keep an eye on **Corbin Carroll**, whose 63.31 score is respectable, though his 4% park penalty against Peterson warrants monitoring as the game progresses.",
